Your Honor,

I, David Lambert, stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I deeply regret my actions and acknowledge that I made a grave error in judgment. As stated in my previous interactions with the courts, I was disqualified from driving 2 months ago due to four speeding incidents.

I understand the consequences of my behavior and accept full responsibility for my thoughtless and irresponsible actions. Despite being fully aware of the court's previous order, I unfortunately failed to consider the fact that I couldn't drive and made the decision to get behind the wheel and drive to a supermarket.

I am genuinely sorry for the embarrassment I have caused myself and for disregarding the court's previous order. I assure you that this incident has been a wake-up call for me. It has made me realize the importance of adhering to the rules and respecting the decisions of the court.

Moving forward, I am committed to making amends and improving myself. I am open to any suggestions or requirements the court may have to rectify this situation. If there is a specific course of action that I can take or guidance that I can seek, whether it be attending a driving course or any other appropriate measures, I am willing to fully comply. My goal is to demonstrate my dedication to personal growth and to ensure that I do not commit any further transgressions.

