Your Honor,

I, David Lambert, humbly stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I deeply regret my actions and acknowledge that my judgment was severely flawed. As previously discussed, I was disqualified from driving two months ago due to four separate incidents of speeding.

I take full responsibility for my reckless behavior and fully understand the gravity of my actions. I deeply apologize for the embarrassment I have caused myself and for disrespecting the court's prior directive. This incident has served as a significant wake-up call for me, emphasizing the importance of respecting the law and adhering to the court's decisions.

I want to assure the court that this incident is an aberration in my otherwise law-abiding life. Throughout my 55 years, I have maintained a good character and have no criminal record. The disqualification from driving is the first and only violation I have encountered. I demonstrate respect for societal norms and laws, and I genuinely regret allowing my lapse of judgment to overshadow my track record of being a responsible and law-abiding citizen.

Looking ahead, I am committed to making amends and improving myself. I am open to any guidance or actions that the court deems appropriate, such as participating in a driving course or any other steps that can demonstrate my commitment to personal growth. I want to assure the court that I understand the seriousness of my actions and I will do everything in my power to ensure that I never repeat such behavior.

Once again, I offer my sincere apologies to the court and to society for my conduct. I appreciate your attention, and I am hopeful that you will consider my previous good character and genuine remorse in your judgement. Thank you, Your Honor.
